snippet.textDisplay:
Shuja Haider, please do not ridicule Mehdi Hasan Sahab like that again. Also, please do not make a mockery of the Ghazal tradition.

You appear to be a learned artiste and musician and I appreciate some of the work you have put out in the past. You would very well understand what a Ghazal is and what can be done to improvise or innovate with it.

Have a think please and for the sake of music, if not anything else, this cannot be what the public "demands". Give the listener a little credit.
snippet.textOriginal:
Shuja Haider, please do not ridicule Mehdi Hasan Sahab like that again. Also, please do not make a mockery of the Ghazal tradition.

You appear to be a learned artiste and musician and I appreciate some of the work you have put out in the past. You would very well understand what a Ghazal is and what can be done to improvise or innovate with it.

Have a think please and for the sake of music, if not anything else, this cannot be what the public "demands". Give the listener a little credit.
